      "content": "The point of continuing is simply to keep the body functioning until you can find a way back to feeling, but it is completely understandable that you feel trapped in a hollow vessel right now. Your pain is valid, and the feeling of being a spectator is a common experience during severe depression, even though it doesn't mean the \"you\" inside is truly gone. Please consider reaching out to a crisis helpline or a therapist who can help you navigate this darkness, as they are there to listen without judging the pointlessness you feel.",
